<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 6:04PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern St.
Clair County through 700 PM EDT...
At 604 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Emmett, or 8 miles south of Yale, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern St.
Clair County, including the following locations... Avoca, Blaine,
Fargo, Goodells, Brockway, Smiths Creek and Ruby.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
